<div dir="ltr">Hi,<div>yep - you can compile OFED/MOFED in the $HOME/ofed dir and point OMPI configure to it with &quot;--with-verbs=/path/to/ofed/install&quot;.</div><div><br></div><div>You can download and compileÂ &quot;libibverbs&quot;,&quot;libibumad&quot;,&quot;libibmad&quot;,&quot;librdmacm&quot;,&quot;opensm&quot;,&quot;infiniband-diags&quot; packages only with custom prefix.</div><div><br></div><div>M</div></div><div class="gmail_extra"><br><div class="gmail_quote">On Fri, Oct 10, 2014 at 11:24 PM, Gary Jackson <span dir="ltr">&lt;<a href="mailto:garyj@cs.umd.edu" target="_blank">garyj@cs.umd.edu</a>&gt;</span> wrote:<br><blockquote class="gmail_quote" style="margin:0 0 0 .8ex;border-left:1px #ccc solid;padding-left:1ex"><br>
